node.text:
“A woman staying in the room in the 1940’s, that’s a big statement... And I think in 2021, it’s still a very powerful one. Women need a place at the table. Women need to stay part of the discussion, because this is how we change the world. ”

We sat down with the A.C. Bradley, the Head Writer on #Marvel's #WhatIf to discuss what happens when women stay in the room! Our interview was led by the one and only @your_pal_bucky 💪

* Marvel’s “What If…?” flips the script on the MCU, reimagining famous events from the films in unexpected ways. Featuring a voice cast that includes a host of stars reprising their roles, Marvel’s What IF is available now on Disney+. *

node.title: Women need a place at the table - Disney's 'What If...?'

node.text:
Sexism with @tova_leigh ☝️

"A few weeks ago I asked you to share with me examples of sexism & casual sexism in your lives. I was inundated by thousands of messages from, mainly women, who shared from their everyday lives examples of sexism and how it affects them. It’s been on my mind ever since... Sexism affects everyone, including men... But the reason I wanted to make this video is because there is a very strong link between sexism and gender inequality and I truly believe that until we break these stereotypes we’ve all been brainwashed to believe, we will struggle to achieve true equality."

Video by @tova_leigh, shared with permission. For more videos like these head over to Tova's page 🙌

#sexism #casualsexism #sexist #inequality #equality #equalpay #misogny #patriarchy #tovaleigh #feminist #feminism #kindness #youmatter #worth #selfworth #believe #empowerment #InspirationalWomen #inspirational #protest #positivevibes #positivity #heforshe #achieve #support #instagood #lesson

node.text:
Meet Kathrine Switzer @kathrineswitzer, the first woman to officially enter The Boston Marathon. Despite being attacked by an official she finished the race and became an activist for women around the world successfully lobbying for the women's marathon to become an Olympic sport 🏃‍♀️

Find out more about Kathrine's work at @261fearless (give them a follow) 🙌❤

node.text:
What is getting in the way of your success and your ability to move forward?

Hear Nada's story and join us at The Rise Leadership Course: https://lnkd.in/dxamEn6 (swipe up in stories or go to our website)

We have come together with Rise Up For You, SHRM-CP, SHRM-SCP to bring you a course designed to take you to the next level. From communication & assertiveness to emotional intelligence, negotiation skills and navigating unconscious bias - now is your chance to step up and invest in yourself.

The course started on the 5th of April but for anyone who missed the early signup, you will be sent the materials and playbacks. The second session is on the 19th so join before then: https://lnkd.in/dGSj5T9, to benefit from a LIVE session with a Q&A and audience coaching.

Rise Up For You are a proud supporter of The Female Lead

node.text:
"In the three short months of 2021, I’ve had more difficult conversations with my kids than I ever had with my own parents.

It breaks my heart to have them, and I don’t know what the right way is, except to falter and and be awkward, and try to process together. My fellow Asian American parents, I’m grieving and standing with you today. Let us better equip our kids for the world they will inherit and shape." 

Video by @janeparkang, shared with permission ❤

#stopasianhate #hateisavirus #stophate

For the first time in history the VP is a woman. Madame Vice President Kamalujah, vice president 🎵 

Put your volume right up because @missymodell is back with another empowering parody 😁

"It only felt fitting to take today to celebrate the FIRST (but not the last!) female, Black, and South Asian Vice President in history 🎉 @vp 

Thank you Madame VP for making it all feel really possible - and a Happy #InternationalWomensDay to all of you brilliant, courageous, and resilient humans 💙

Written with @scottsimonsmusic 
Vocal mix & vocal mix: @mattbeilis

"To illustrate how insane a 6-week abortion ban is: I did IVF and still did not know I was pregnant until 4.5 weeks. That's LITERALLY as early as you can possibly know and that's when you are PAYING someone to put an embryo in your body on a specific day and keep track of it." 
Tweet by Lucy Huber @clhubes on Twitter

#feminist #youmatter #worth #abortion #protest #support #feminim #abortionban

That's LITERALLY as early as you can possibly know and that's when you are PAYING someone to put an embryo in your body on a specific day and keep track of it.'.

Photo by The Female Lead on September 02, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Lucy Huber @clhubes But obviously, this is the point, right? A 6-week abortion ban is a total abortion ban, because pretty much the only people who could reasonably get an abortion are people who very much want to be pregnant.'.

node.text:
‘When Are You Having a Baby?’ "You'll change your mind?" - What questions or comments have you received about your decision to have children?

Women who don't have children are often met with questions or assurances that they’ll "change their mind". But the fact is: it’s nobody’s business! More and more people are choosing not to have kids and that's okay! 

Comment below and join in the discussion with our friends @femalequotient

#childfree #feminist #feminism #choices #empoweredwomen #childfreebychoice #noneofyourbusiness

"When you are a comedian and a gold medallist" 😅🥇 by @kelsey.mitchell9 🙌

"Classic Kels 😎😏🥇
Shoutout to Japan! I did not see much of this country…I didn’t even have sushi 🍱🥺!!!
BUT the people were INCREDIBLE! So kind, polite, helpful, positive, friendly, AND they even laughed at my jokes (bonus!!) 😅😅 
Thank you Japan for hosting the Olympics, for allowing people to follow and accomplish their dreams, and to show the world the power of sport! ❤️🇯🇵 "
🎥 @hugebarrette 

With thanks to Kelsey for allowing us to share and @womenofimpact who also shared 😍
